<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id13aa6c92-3a70-11f1-b089-c1e1e512a22d" identifier="/us/usc/t21/s214"><num value="214">§ 214.</num><heading> Previous laws unaffected</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">Nothing in this chapter shall be construed as modifying or revoking any of the provisions of sections 191 to 193 <ref class="footnoteRef" idref="fn002003">1</ref><note type="footnote" id="fn002003"><num>1</num> See References in Text note below.</note> of this title.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="id13aa6c93-3a70-11f1-b089-c1e1e512a22d">(<ref href="/us/act/1915-03-03/ch74/s13">Mar. 3, 1915, ch. 74, § 13</ref>, <ref href="/us/stat/38/822">38 Stat. 822</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
<notes type="uscNote" id="id13aa6c94-3a70-11f1-b089-c1e1e512a22d">
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" role="crossHeading" topic="editorialNotes" id="id13aa6c95-3a70-11f1-b089-c1e1e512a22d"><heading class="centered"><b>Editorial Notes</b></heading></note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I75" topic="referencesInText" id="id13aa6c96-3a70-11f1-b089-c1e1e512a22d">
<heading class="centered smallCaps">References in Text</heading><p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">Sections 191 to 193 of this title, referred to in text, were repealed by <ref href="/us/pl/91/513/tIII/s1101/a/1">Pub. L. 91–513, title III, § 1101(a)(1)</ref>, <date date="1970-10-27">Oct. 27, 1970</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/84/1291">84 Stat. 1291</ref>. See section 801 et seq. of this title.</p>
</note>
